              "uco-observable:stringValue": "Query Reports Utilities Help Log Out\n\nCLOSED,Mandarin INTERPRETER\n\nU.S. District Court\nCalifornia Northern District (San Francisco)\nCRIMINAL DOCKET FOR CASE #: 3:20-cr-00446-WHA All Defendants\n\nCase title: USA v. Li Date Filed: 12/01/2020\n\nAssigned to: Judge William Alsup\n\nDefendant (1)\nHan Li\nalso known as\nHan Li Anson\n\nPending Counts Disposition\n50:1705 and 15 CFR Parts 764(d) Conspiracy to violate IEEPA\n(1)\n13:305 and 18:2 Unlawful export information activities\n(2)\n18:554 and 2 Smuggling of goods\n(3)\n50:1705 and 18:2 and 15:764(2),(a),(b),(c)and(e) Willful\nviolations of IEEPA\n(4)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Opening)\nFelony\n\nTerminated Counts Disposition\nNone\n\nHighest Offense Level (Terminated)\nNone\nComplaints Disposition\nNone\n\nAssigned to: Judge William Alsup\n\nDefendant (2)\nLin Chen represented by Miranda Kane\nTERMINATED: 01/28/2025 Conrad Metlitzky Kane LLP\n217 Leidesdorff Street\nSan Francisco, CA 94111\n415-469-1714\nFax: 415-343-7101\nEmail: mkane@conmetkane.com\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Retained\n\nGrace Yu-Ting Yang\nConrad Metlitzky Kane LLP\n217 Leidesdorff Street\nSan Francisco, CA 94111\n415-469-1715\nFax: 415-343-7101\nEmail: gyang@conmetkane.com\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Retained\n\nPending Counts Disposition\nParties stated appearances and proffered argument. Defendant's\nallocution relayed through counsel. Court imposed the\nfollowing sentence: Defendant sentenced to 4 months BOP\n50:1705 and 18:2 and 15:764(2),(a),(b),(c)and(e) Willful\ncustody on Count 4 of the Indictment; 1 year supervised release\nviolations of IEEPA\n(but likely deported); $5,000 fine; $100 special assessment.\n(4)\nCourt strongly recommends defendant be housed at FCI Waseca\n- Minnesota - or a facility that has ready access to a Mandarin\ninterpreter, keeping in mind the\\ defendant's impaired health.\n\nHighest Offense Level (Opening)\nFelony\nTerminated Counts Disposition\n50:1705 and 15 CFR Parts 764(d) Conspiracy to violate IEEPA\nDismissed by oral motion by Government.\n(1)\n13:305 and 18:2 Unlawful export information activities\nDismissed by oral motion by Government.\n(2)\n18:554 and 2 Smuggling of goods\nDismissed by oral motion by Government.\n(3)\n\nHighest Offense Level (Terminated)\nFelony\n\nComplaints Disposition\nNone\n\nPlaintiff\nUSA represented by Colin Christopher Sampson\nU.S. Department of Justice, United States Attorney's Of\nNorthern District of California, Tax Division\n450 Golden Gate Avenue\nBox 36055\nSan Francisco, CA 94102\n(415) 436-7020\nFax: (415) 436-7009\nEmail: colin.sampson@usdoj.gov\nLEAD ATTORNEY\nATTORNEY TO BE NOTICED\nDesignation: Assistant US Attorney\n\nDate Filed # Docket Text\n12/01/2020 1 INDICTMENT as to Han Li (1) count(s) 1, 2, 3, 4, Lin Chen (2) count(s) 1, 2, 3, 4. (lskS, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 12/1/2020) (tn,\nCOURT STAFF). (Entered: 12/01/2020)\n12/01/2020 2 Motion to Seal by USA as to Han Li, Lin Chen (lskS, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 12/1/2020) (tn, COURT STAFF). (Entered: 12/01/2020)\n12/01/2020 3 Order to Seal Case as to Han Li, Lin Chen. Signed by Magistrate Judge Laurel Beeler on 12/1/2020. Clerk of Court shall provide\ncopies of the sealed documents to employees of the United States Attorneys Office. (lskS, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 12/1/2020)\nModified on 12/1/2020 (lskS, COURT STAFF). (tn, COURT STAFF). (Entered: 12/01/2020)\n04/24/2024 4 APPLICATION by USA. ORDER Granting Application to Unseal Case. Signed by Magistrate Judge Alex G. Tse on 4/24/2024. (exl,\nCOURT STAFF) (Filed on 4/24/2024) Modified on 5/9/2024 (tn, COURT STAFF). M (Entered: 04/25/2024)\n05/08/2024 5 Rule 5(c)(3)Documents Received as to Lin Chen from Northern District of Illinois. (Attachments: # 1 Commitment to Another District, # 2\nOrder)(tn, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/8/2024) (Entered: 05/09/2024)\n05/09/2024 Set Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen: Initial Appearance set for 5/10/2024 at 10:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom C, 15th Floor before\nMagistrate Judge Sallie Kim. (bxl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/9/2024) (Entered: 05/09/2024)\n05/10/2024 Set Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen: Status Conference set for 5/13/2024 at 10:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom C, 15th Floor before\nMagistrate Judge Sallie Kim. (bxl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/10/2024) (Entered: 05/10/2024)\n05/10/2024 6 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim: Arraignment as to Lin Chen (2) on Counts 1,2,3,4 of the Indictment\nheld on 5/10/2024. Plea entered by Lin Chen (2), Counts 1,2,3,4 by Lin Chen Not Guilty on counts 1-4 of the Indictment. Interpreter\nNeeded in case as to Lin Chen.Added attorney Miranda Kane for Lin Chen. Advised of Rights. Advised of Charges. Reading Waived\nSubstance. Remanded to Custody.\n\nThe Court directs entry of the following Order: Pursuant to the Due Process Protection Act, the Court advised government counsel of the\ngovernment's disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland and its progeny, and that the failure to do so in a timely manner may result in\ndismissal of the indictment or information, dismissal of individual charges, exclusion of government evidence or witnesses, or any other\nremedy that is just under the circumstances.\n\nGov seeks detention. Bail study has been conducted in previous district. The Court did not receive a copy of report. Def does not agree with\ndetention. Proffers heard. Previously in custody in Chicago. Def proposes a $100,000 cash bond be signed by a surety, surety to be\ninterviewed by PTS on 5/10/2024. The Marshals are to give Ms. Chen warmer clothes. Gov. previously filed to unseal indictment. Time\nexclusion from 5/10/2024 to 5/13/2024, granted. Status Conference re Detention set for 5/13/2024 at 10:30 AM in San Francisco,\nCourtroom C, 15th Floor before Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim. Recording Time: 10:42-10:54. (tn, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/10/2024)\n(Entered: 05/10/2024)\n05/10/2024 7 STIPULATED ORDER EXCLUDING TIME UNDER THE SPEEDY TRIAL ACT AND WAIVER UNDER FRCP 5.1 from\n5/10/2024 to 5/13/2024 as to Lin Chen. Signed by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim on 5/10/2024. (tn, COURT STAFF) (Filed on\n5/10/2024) (Entered: 05/10/2024)\n05/13/2024 9 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release Personal Recognizance and Appearance Bond Entered as to Lin Chen in the amount of\n$200,000. Signed by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim on 5/13/2024. (tn, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/13/2024) (Entered: 05/13/2024)\n05/13/2024 10 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim: Detention Hearing as to Lin Chen held on 5/13/2024. Issued\n$200,000 Appearance Bond. Amount of Security $100,000. Passport Surrendered Date 5/13/2024. Gov seeks detention. Proffers heard.\nChen Chen, proposed custodian, made an appearance on the record. The Court added, electronic monitoring and Ms. Chen has to be 2 miles\naway from international airports except if she is traveling on the 101 freeway, as bond conditions. Passport was previously surrendered in\nChicago. Defendant and custodian admonished re bond conditions. Bond signed in court on 5/13/2024. Time excluded from 5/13/24 to\n6/11/24. Status Conference set for 6/11/2024 at 02:00 PM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup.\nRecording Time: 11 :10-11 :26. (tn, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/13/2024) (Entered: 05/13/2024)\n05/13/2024 11 STIPULATED ORDER EXCLUDING TIME UNDER THE SPEEDY TRIAL ACT AND WAIVER UNDER FRCP 5.1 from\n5/13/2024 to 6/11/2024 as to Lin Chen. Signed by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim on 5/13/2024. (tn, COURT STAFF) (Filed on\n5/13/2024) (Entered: 05/13/2024)\n05/13/2024 12 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Grace Yu-Ting Yang appearing for Lin Chen (Yang, Grace) (Filed on 5/13/2024) (Entered:\n05/13/2024)\n05/14/2024 16 Receipt in the amount of $ $100,000.00 from Lin Chen; Date receipt issued on 05/13/2024 with Receipt # 311168875 (rgh, COURT\nSTAFF) (Filed on 5/14/2024) (Entered: 05/22/2024)\n05/15/2024 Set Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen: Status Conference set for 5/21/2024 at 10:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom C, 15th Floor before\nMagistrate Judge Sallie Kim. (bxl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/15/2024) (Entered: 05/15/2024)\n05/16/2024 13 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen to Modifying Conditions of Pre-Trial Release. (Kane, Miranda) (Filed on\n5/16/2024) (Entered: 05/16/2024)\n05/16/2024 14 Order by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim granting 13 Stipulation Modifying Conditions of Pre-Trial Release as to Lin Chen (2). (bxl,\nCOURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/16/2024) (Entered: 05/16/2024)\n05/17/2024 15 Arrest Warrant Returned Executed on 4/24/2024 as to Lin Chen. (exl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 5/17/2024) (Entered: 05/20/2024)\n05/21/2024 19 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim: Status Conference as to Lin Chen held on 5/21/2024. The Court\nadded additional release conditions. The government shall prepare a proposed order. Digital Recording Time 10:47-10:53. (bxl, COURT\nSTAFF) (Filed on 5/21/2024) (Entered: 05/31/2024)\n05/24/2024 17 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen filed by USA. (Sampson, Colin) (Filed on 5/24/2024) (Entered: 05/24/2024)\n05/28/2024 18 Order by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim granting 17 Stipulation Modifying Conditions of Release as to Lin Chen (2). (bxl, COURT\nSTAFF) (Filed on 5/28/2024) (Entered: 05/28/2024)\n06/05/2024 20 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen Stipulation And Protective Order [Proposed] filed by USA. (Sampson, Colin)\n(Filed on 6/5/2024) (Entered: 06/05/2024)\n06/05/2024 21 ORDER GRANTING 20 STIPULATION AND PROTECTIVE ORDER AS TO LIN CHEN. Signed by Judge Alsup. (whalc1,\nCOURT STAFF) (Filed on 6/5/2024) (Entered: 06/05/2024)\n06/06/2024 22 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen Stipulated Motion To Continue Status And To Exclude Time Under The Speedy\nTrial Act [Proposed] Order filed by USA. (Sampson, Colin) (Filed on 6/6/2024) (Entered: 06/06/2024)\n06/10/2024 23 ORDER GRANTING 22 STIPULATED MOTION TO CONTINUE STATUS AND TO EXCLUDE TIME UNDER THE SPEEDY\nTRIAL ACT as to Lin Chen (2). Status Conference continued to specially set time 7/2/2024 at 9:00AM. Signed by Judge William\nAlsup on 6/10/2024. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Entered: 06/10/2024)\n06/10/2024 Set/Reset Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen re 23 Order on Stipulation: Status Conference set for 7/2/2024 09:00 AM in San Francisco,\nCourtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 6/10/2024) (Entered: 06/10/2024)\n07/01/2024 24 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen to Continue Status Conference and Exclude Time Under the Speedy Trial Act.\n(Kane, Miranda) (Filed on 7/1/2024) (Entered: 07/01/2024)\n07/01/2024 25 ORDER GRANTING 24 STIPULATION TO CONTINUE STATUS CONFERENCE AND EXCLUDE TIME UNDER THE\nSPEEDY TRIAL ACT as to Lin Chen (2). Status Conference set for 7/2/2024 is continued to 7/23/2024 at 11:00AM. Signed by Judge\nWilliam Alsup on 7/1/2024. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Entered: 07/01/2024)\n07/01/2024 Set/Reset Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen re 25 Order on Stipulation, Status Conference reset for 7/23/2024 11:00 AM in San Francisco,\nCourtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 7/1/2024) (Entered: 07/01/2024)\n07/23/2024 26 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William Alsup:\n\nStatus Conference as to Lin Chen held on 7/23/2024. Government stated that discovery is voluminous and it has provided defendant\nwith some discovery thus far. It will further provide the remaining discovery to defendant. Court set trial and pretrial conference.\nTime excluded for effective preparation of counsel. Government to submit proposed exclusion order. Jury Selection/Jury Trial set\nfor 12/9/2024 07:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup. Further Status Conference set for\n9/3/2024 10:00 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup.\n\nTotal Time in Court 11:03 - 11:07 = 4 Minutes.\nCourt Reporter: Kendra Steppler (remote).\n\nPlaintiff Attorney: Colin Sampson.\nDefendant Attorney: Grace Yang.\n\nDefendant Present: Yes. Defendant in Custody: No.\nInterpreter: Yongmei Liu, sworn. Language: Mandarin\n\nExcludable Delay: Yes. Begins: 7/23/2024. Ends: 12/4/2024.\n\n(This is a text-only entry generated by the court. There is no document associated with this entry.) (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on\n7/23/2024) (Entered: 07/24/2024)\n08/15/2024 27 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen Stipulated Motion To Exclude Time Under The Speedy Trial Act [Proposed]\nOrder filed by USA. (Sampson, Colin) (Filed on 8/15/2024) (Entered: 08/15/2024)\n08/16/2024 28 ORDER GRANTING 27 STIPULATED MOTION TO EXCLUDE TIME UNDER THE SPEEDY TRIAL ACT as to Lin Chen (2).\nSigned by Judge William Alsup on 8/16/2024. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Entered: 08/16/2024)\n08/26/2024 29 CLERK'S NOTICE RESCHEDULING STATUS CONFERENCE FROM 9/3/2024 TO 9/10/2024 AT SPECIALLY SET TIME\n9:00AM as to Lin Chen: Status Conference RESET for 9/10/2024 09:00 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before\nJudge William Alsup. (This is a text-only entry generated by the court. There is no document associated with this entry.) (afm, COURT\nSTAFF) (Filed on 8/26/2024) (Entered: 08/26/2024)\n08/28/2024 Set/Reset Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen re 26 Status Conference: Pretrial Conference set for 12/4/2024 12:00 PM in San Francisco,\nCourtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 8/28/2024) (Entered: 08/28/2024)\n09/10/2024 30 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William Alsup:\n\nStatus Conference as to Lin Chen held on 9/10/2024. Parties requested additional time for ongoing discussions. Court vacated trial\ndate of 12/10/2024 and RESET Jury Selection/Jury Trial for 1/6/2025 07:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before\nJudge William Alsup. Time excluded to 1/6/2025. Government to submit a proposed exclusion order. Further Status Conference set\nfor 10/8/2024 11:00 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup.\n\nTotal Time in Court 9:18 - 9:22 = 4 Minutes.\nCourt Reporter: Ruth Ekhaus.\n\nPlaintiff Attorney: Colin Sampson.\nDefendant Attorneys: Miranda Kane, Grace Yang.\n\nDefendant Present: Yes. Defendant in Custody: No.\nInterpreter: Jeff Dinn, sworn. Language: Mandarin.\nExcludable Delay: Yes. Begins: 9/10/2024. Ends: 1/6/2025.\n(This is a text-only entry generated by the court. There is no document associated with this entry.) (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on\n9/10/2024) (Entered: 09/11/2024)\n10/01/2024 31 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen to Continue Status Conference. (Kane, Miranda) (Filed on 10/1/2024)\n(Entered: 10/01/2024)\n10/02/2024 32 ORDER GRANTING 31 STIPULATION TO CONTINUE STATUS CONFERENCE as to Lin Chen (2). Status Conference reset to\n10/15/2024 at 2:00PM before Judge William Alsup, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor, San Francisco, CA. Signed by Judge William Alsup\non 10/2/2024. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Entered: 10/02/2024)\n10/02/2024 Set/Reset Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen re 32 Order on Stipulation: Status Conference set for 10/15/2024 02:00 PM in San Francisco,\nCourtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 10/2/2024) (Entered: 10/02/2024)\n10/15/2024 33 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William Alsup:\n\nStatus Conference as to Lin Chen held on 10/15/2024. Defense counsel handed up signed Plea Agreement to Court. Defendant\nsworn and advised of rights. Due to further clarification as stated on the record, Court reset Change of Plea hearing to Thursday,\n10/17/2024, at 2:00PM. Change of Plea Hearing set for 10/17/2024 02:00 PM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before\nJudge William Alsup.\n\nTotal Time in Court 2:03 - 2:28 = 25 Minutes.\nCourt Reporter: Ruth Ekhaus.\n\nPlaintiff Attorney: Colin Sampson.\nDefendant Attorneys: Miranda Kane, Grace Yang.\n\nDefendant Present: Yes. Defendant in Custody: No.\nInterpreter: Shan Tsen. Language: Mandarin, Sworn.\n\n(This is a text-only entry generated by the court. There is no document associated with this entry.) (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on\n10/15/2024) (Entered: 10/15/2024)\n10/17/2024 34 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William Alsup:\n\nChange of Plea Hearing as to Lin Chen held on 10/17/2024. Plea entered by Lin Chen (2) Guilty Count 4. Sentencing set for\n1/28/2025 11:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom 12, 19th Floor before Judge William Alsup. See pdf image for further details.\n\nTotal Time in Court 2:05 - 2:53 = 48 Minutes.\nCourt Reporter: Lee-Anne Shortridge (remote).\nPlaintiff Attorney: Colin Sampson.\nDefendant Attorneys: Miranda Kane, Grace Yang.\n\nDefendant Present: Yes. Defendant in Custody: No.\nInterpreter: Amanda Peeters, sworn. Language: Mandarin.\nAttachment Minute Order.\nExcludable Delay: No. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 10/17/2024) (Entered: 10/18/2024)\n10/17/2024 35 PLEA AGREEMENT (dated 10/15/2024) as to Lin Chen. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 10/17/2024) (Entered: 10/18/2024)\n10/17/2024 36 PLEA AGREEMENT (dated 10/17/2024) as to Lin Chen. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 10/17/2024) (Entered: 10/18/2024)\n10/23/2024 37 TRANSCRIPT ORDER for proceedings held on 10/15/2024 before Judge William Alsup for Court Reporter Ruth Ekhaus (Yang, Grace)\n(Filed on 10/23/2024) (Entered: 10/23/2024)\n10/23/2024 38 TRANSCRIPT ORDER for proceedings held on 10/17/2024 before Judge William Alsup for Court Reporter Lee-Anne Shortridge (Yang,\nGrace) (Filed on 10/23/2024) (Entered: 10/23/2024)\n10/29/2024 39 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen Modifying Conditions of Pre-Trial Release; Request for Further Hearing.\n(Kane, Miranda) (Filed on 10/29/2024) (Entered: 10/29/2024)\n10/29/2024 40 Order by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim granting 39 Stipulation to Modify Release Conditions as to Lin Chen (2). Bail Review\nHearing set for 11/7/2024 at 9:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom C, 15th Floor before Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim. (bxl, COURT\nSTAFF) (Filed on 10/29/2024) (Entered: 10/29/2024)\n10/29/2024 Set Hearing as to Defendant Lin Chen: Bail Review Hearing set for 11/7/2024 at 9:30 AM in San Francisco, Courtroom C, 15th Floor\nbefore Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim. (bxl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 10/29/2024) (Entered: 10/29/2024)\n11/05/2024 41 STATUS REPORT Regarding Travel to Western District of Wisconsin by Lin Chen (Yang, Grace) (Filed on 11/5/2024) (Entered:\n11/05/2024)\n11/07/2024 42 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim: Bail Review Hearing as to Lin Chen held on 11/7/2024. An order\nreleasing Ms. Chen's passport to her daughter and a modified bond were signed in court. Recording Time 9:37-9:47. Interpreter: Amanda\nPeeters (Sworn). (bxl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 11/7/2024) (Entered: 11/07/2024)\n11/07/2024 43 ORDER TO RELEASE PASSPORT as to Lin Chen. Signed by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim on 11/7/2024. (bxl, COURT STAFF)\n(Filed on 11/7/2024) (Entered: 11/07/2024)\n11/07/2024 44 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release Secured Bond Entered as to Lin Chen in amount of $ 200,000. Signed by Magistrate Judge\nSallie Kim on 11/7/2024. (bxl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 11/7/2024) (Entered: 11/07/2024)\n11/17/2024 45 Transcript of Proceedings as to Han Li, Lin Chen held on 10/15/2024, before Judge William Alsup. Court Reporter Ruth Levine Ekhaus,\nRMR, RDR, FCRR, CSR No. 12219, telephone number ruth_ekhaus@cand.uscourts.gov/(415)336-5223. Per General Order No. 59 and\nJudicial Conference policy, this transcript may be viewed only at the Clerk's Office public terminal or may be purchased through the Court\nReporter until the deadline for the Release of Transcript Restriction. After that date it may be obtained through PACER. Any Notice of\nIntent to Request Redaction, if required, is due no later than 5 business days from date of this filing. Release of Transcript Restriction set for\n2/18/2025. (Related documents(s) 37 ) (rre, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 11/17/2024) (Entered: 11/17/2024)\n12/04/2024 46 Transcript of Proceedings as to Lin Chen held on 10-17-24, before Judge William H. Alsup. Court Reporter Lee-Anne Shortridge, email:\nlee-anne_shortridge@cand.uscourts.gov. Per General Order No. 59 and Judicial Conference policy, this transcript may be viewed only at\nthe Clerk's Office public terminal or may be purchased through the Court Reporter until the deadline for the Release of Transcript\nRestriction. After that date it may be obtained through PACER. Any Notice of Intent to Request Redaction, if required, is due no later than\n5 business days from date of this filing. Release of Transcript Restriction set for 3/4/2025. (Related documents(s) 38 ) (las, COURT STAFF)\n(Filed on 12/4/2024) (Entered: 12/04/2024)\n01/21/2025 48 SENTENCING MEMORANDUM by USA as to Lin Chen (Sampson, Colin) (Filed on 1/21/2025) (Entered: 01/21/2025)\n01/21/2025 49 SENTENCING MEMORANDUM by Lin Chen (Attachments: # 1 Declaration of Grace Yang in Support of Defendant Lin Chen's\nSentencing Memorandum, # 2 Declaration of Joel A. Sickler in Support of Defendant Lin Chen's Sentencing Memorandum)(Kane,\nMiranda) (Filed on 1/21/2025) (Entered: 01/21/2025)\n01/28/2025 53 REQUEST FOR INFORMATION. Signed by Judge Alsup. (whalc1, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 1/28/2025) (Entered: 01/28/2025)\n01/28/2025 54 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge William Alsup:\n\nSentencing held on 1/28/2025 for Lin Chen (2), Count(s) 1, 2, 3, Dismissed by oral motion by Government; Count(s) 4: Court\nimposed the following sentence: Defendant sentenced to 4 months BOP custody on Count 4 of the Indictment; 1 year supervised\nrelease (but likely deported); $5,000 fine; $100 special assessment. Court strongly recommends defendant be housed at FCI Waseca\n- Minnesota - or a facility that has ready access to a Mandarin interpreter, keeping in mind the defendant's impaired health.\n\nTotal Time in Court 11:30 - 12:35 = 1 Hour; 5 Minutes.\nCourt Reporter: Debra Pas.\n\nPlaintiff Attorney: Colin Sampson.\nDefendant Attorneys: Miranda Kane, Grace Yang.\nAlso Present: Family and friends of defendant.\nProbation Officer: Denise Mancia.\n\nDefendant Present: Yes. Defendant in Custody: No.\nInterpreter: Amanda Peeters, sworn. Language: Mandarin.\n\nAttachment Minute Order.\nExcludable Delay: No. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 1/28/2025) (Entered: 01/28/2025)\n02/03/2025 55 JUDGMENT in a Criminal Case as to Lin Chen. Signed by Judge William Alsup on 2/3/2025. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Filed on\n2/3/2025) (Entered: 02/03/2025)\n03/10/2025 57 PAYMENT RECORD CARD : payment of Special Assessment in the amount of $100.00 paid on 03/05/2025 on behalf of Lin Chen (rgh,\nCOURT STAFF) (Filed on 3/10/2025) (Entered: 03/10/2025)\n03/26/2025 58 STIPULATION WITH PROPOSED ORDER as to Lin Chen to Return Defendants Passport to Defense Counsel. (Kane, Miranda) (Filed on\n3/26/2025) (Entered: 03/26/2025)\n03/26/2025 59 Order by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim granting 58 Stipulation to Return Defendants Passport to Defense Counsel as to Lin Chen\n(2). (bxl, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 3/26/2025) (Entered: 03/26/2025)\n04/03/2025 60 Proposed Order by Lin Chen to Exonerate Bond (Kane, Miranda) (Filed on 4/3/2025) (Entered: 04/03/2025)\n04/03/2025 61 ORDER TO EXONERATE BOND as to Lin Chen. Signed by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim on 4/3/2025. (bxl, COURT STAFF)\n(Filed on 4/3/2025) (Entered: 04/03/2025)\n04/03/2025 62 MOTION for Reconsideration re 61 Order to Exonerate Bond and For Payment of Fine from Bond Funds by USA as to Lin Chen.\n(Sampson, Colin) (Filed on 4/3/2025) (Entered: 04/03/2025)\n06/09/2025 63 MOTION to Reconvey Exonerated Bond by Lin Chen as to Han Li, Lin Chen. (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit A)(Kane, Miranda) (Filed on\n6/9/2025) (Entered: 06/09/2025)\n06/09/2025 64 ORDER GRANTING 63 MOTION TO RECONVEY EXONERATED BOND as to Lin Chen (2). Signed by Magistrate Judge Sallie\nKim on 6/9/2025. (afm, COURT STAFF) (Entered: 06/09/2025)\n06/10/2025 65 Amended MOTION for Bond Request to Reconvey Exonerated Bond (related to Dkt. 63) by Lin Chen. (Kane, Miranda) (Filed on\n6/10/2025) (Entered: 06/10/2025)\n06/10/2025 66 ORDER GRANTING 65 AMENDED MOTION FOR BOND as to Lin Chen (2). Signed by Judge William Alsup on 6/10/2025.\n(afm, COURT STAFF) (Entered: 06/10/2025)\n07/24/2025 67 Amended MOTION for Bond Request to Reconvey Exonerated Bond (related to Dkt. 65) by Lin Chen. (Kane, Miranda) (Filed on\n7/24/2025) (Entered: 07/24/2025)\n07/24/2025 68 Order by Magistrate Judge Sallie Kim granting 67 Amended Motion to Reconvey Exonerated Bond as to Lin Chen (2). (bxl,\nCOURT STAFF) (Filed on 7/24/2025) (Entered: 07/24/2025)\n03/09/2026 69 PAYMENT RECORD CARD : payment of Fine in the amount of $5,000.00 principal plus $25.00 interest paid on 07/10/2025 on behalf of\nLin Chen (rgh, COURT STAFF) (Filed on 3/9/2026) (Entered: 03/09/2026)\n\nPACER Service Center\nTransaction Receipt\n06/27/2026 16:16:44\nPACER\nmrinaal_ramachandran Client Code:\nLogin:\nSearch 3:20-cr-00446-\nDescription: Docket Report\nCriteria: WHA\nBillable\n9 Cost: 0.90\nPages:"
